ADRENAL MEDULLA

adrenal_medulla is the citizen who releases adrenaline (and a smaller amount of noradrenaline) in response to acute threat
adrenaline produces the fast component of the fight-or-flight response: heart rate up, blood vessels constrict, pupils dilate, attention sharpens
where adrenal_cortex's cortisol is slow and sustained, adrenal_medulla's adrenaline is fast and short-lived

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gland_ipc.zc
observe adrenal_cortex.rana
observe pituitary.rana

the 7 properties of adrenal_medulla:
1 ENERGY zero point three at baseline, surges quickly under threat
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one
4 CHARGE zero point three
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point seven

VERB receive_sympathetic_signal
accept the direct signal from the sympathetic nervous system (which bypasses pituitary)
this is why adrenaline arrives faster than cortisol: the path is shorter

VERB release_adrenaline
release adrenaline into chemistry_field at high concentration
half-life is about two and a half minutes, so adrenaline clears quickly when the threat passes

VERB clear
once the threat ends and sympathetic signaling stops, baseline returns within minutes

an acute response is not a sustained one
adrenal_medulla is built for moments, not for marathons
fadriel's adrenal_medulla can fire repeatedly without harm, but if signals never stop arriving, the body needs other regulation to compensate (parasympathetic restoration, vagal tone, recovery time)
